      "markdown": "## T-0981 [x] P3: Нормализовать сериализацию `evidence metadata command`\n\n- Создана: 2026-07-05T19:31:45+03:00\n- Состояние: accepted/closed\n- Приоритет: P3\n- Execution class: `internal-substrate`\n- Scheduling tier: `later`\n- Зависимости: T-0239\n- Ссылки:\n  - Доменный документ: `docs/release-management/audit-package.md`\n  - Исходный код: `eng/Electron2D.Build/AuditPackageCommand.cs`\n  - Исходный код: `eng/Electron2D.Build/AuditSubmitCommand.cs`\n  - Тесты: `tests/Electron2D.Tests.Integration/RepositoryBuildToolTests.cs`\n  - Verdict: `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0981-audit-r01.md`\n  - Источник: `RISKS_AND_NOTES` из `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0239-audit-r02.md`\n\n### Execution contract\n\n- Task type: production\n- Ready-to-start:\n  - task state is `open` or an explicitly defined ready state.\n  - dependencies are accepted/closed or have explicit `Deferred`/`Unsupported` contract.\n  - `docs/release-management/audit-package.md` is current and a focused RED test or verifier can be added before production changes.\n- Stop conditions:\n  - fixing the issue would require changing the accepted `T-0239` scope instead of the evidence metadata serialization path.\n  - generated evidence format is intentionally changed without updating the domain document and tests.\n  - the change would hide the command instead of making `metadata.json.command` consistent with `command.txt`.\n- May change:\n  - the audit-package evidence metadata writer and its owning tests/docs.\n  - generated documentation index through `update docs` only if the domain document changes.\n  - `TASKS.md` notes and diary entries for this task.\n- Must not change:\n  - external audit verdict reports, past evidence files or saved audit archives.\n  - unrelated `audit submit` browser automation behavior.\n  - public API surface, release gates or task graph outside this follow-up.\n- Required outputs:\n  - updated domain contract for evidence metadata command serialization.\n  - RED/GREEN focused test or verifier proving `metadata.json.command` agrees with `command.txt`.\n  - task notes and diary entries with exact command results.\n- Required commands:\n  - `dotnet build eng/Electron2D.Build/Electron2D.Build.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal`\n  - focused integration test or verifier for generated preflight evidence metadata.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- verify audit-followups`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- verify docs`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- update docs --check`\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- verify licenses` when C# source changes.\n  - `git diff --check`\n- External audit:\n  - primary external audit required for final acceptance; first-try primary `ACCEPT` is treated as control-equivalent by explicit operator decision on 2026-07-07.\n\n### Самодостаточное описание\n\nPrimary audit `T-0239` r02 принял удаление screenshot recorder, но нашёл follow-up в служебном evidence metadata: поле `evidence/**/metadata.json.command` записывало команду с потерей пробела между executable и первым аргументом, например `dotnetrun`, `dotnetbuild`, `dotnettest`, `gitdiff`. Соседние `command.txt`, `metadata/audit-package.input.json`, stdout/stderr и exit code оставались достаточными для проверки пакета, поэтому это не было blocker `T-0239`, но формат metadata нужно было нормализовать отдельной задачей.\n\nИтоговый результат: новые audit packages переписывают root preflight `metadata.json.command` в staging-копии evidence так, чтобы он совпадал с configured command и `command.txt`. Исторические ZIP и сохранённые evidence-файлы не переписываются; совместимость старых пакетов остаётся на verifier-уровне.\n\n### Internal substrate acceptance contract\n\n- Evidence metadata has deterministic serialization and fail-closed tests for command fields.\n- `command.txt` remains the canonical human-readable command evidence, while `metadata.json.command` stays consistent with it instead of becoming a lossy duplicate.\n- Existing audit package verification remains compatible with old saved packages; the new rule applies to newly generated evidence.\n- This task does not change audit verdict parsing, browser submission or public runtime behavior.\n\n### Критерии приёмки\n\n- [x] `docs/release-management/audit-package.md` documents the expected relationship between `command.txt` and `metadata.json.command`.\n- [x] Focused tests or verifier generate representative preflight evidence and prove `metadata.json.command` does not lose spaces or quoting relative to `command.txt`.\n- [x] The fix covers commands beginning with `dotnet run`, `dotnet build`, `dotnet test` and `git diff`.\n- [x] Existing audit package verification remains compatible with saved packages and current package evidence.\n- [x] `verify audit-followups` passes with the closure note from `T-0239` r02.\n\n### Подзадачи\n\n- [x] Add a RED regression around generated evidence metadata command serialization.\n- [x] Update the evidence metadata writer with the smallest compatible representation.\n- [x] Update the domain document and generated documentation index when the contract changes.\n- [x] Run focused tests, docs checks, license verifier when needed, `verify audit-followups` and `git diff --check`.\n\n### Current evidence\n\n- Ready-to-start gate:\n  - `T-0981` started from `open` state.\n  - dependency `T-0239` was accepted/closed in this archive with saved `VERDICT: ACCEPT` reports `t-0239-audit-r02.md` and `t-0239-audit-control-r02.md`.\n  - no external blocker without user override was present.\n- RED/GREEN:\n  - `AuditPackageNormalizesPreflightMetadataCommandToConfiguredCommand` first failed 4/4 on lossy `dotnetrun`, `dotnetbuild`, `dotnettest` and `gitdiff`.\n  - after the fix, the focused test passed 4/4 and the no-build rerun passed 4/4.\n- Local checks before audit:\n  - `dotnet build eng/Electron2D.Build/Electron2D.Build.csproj --no-restore -v:minimal` passed, warnings `0`.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- verify audit-contracts` passed, Fast `12/12`.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- update docs --check` passed.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- verify docs` passed.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- verify audit-followups` passed for `31` actionable findings across `152` saved reports.\n  - `dotnet run --project eng/Electron2D.Build --no-build --no-restore -- verify licenses` passed for `664` source files.\n  - `git diff --check` passed.\n- External audit:\n  - primary package `.temp/audit/T-0981-audit-r01.zip` was created by `audit package` and verified by operator workflow.\n  - primary report `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0981-audit-r01.md` was saved by `audit submit` with `VERDICT: ACCEPT`.\n  - `RISKS_AND_NOTES` in the saved report are `None`.\n  - clean-control package was created and operator-verified, but no control submit was run after the user's explicit 2026-07-07 decision that first-try primary `ACCEPT` is control-equivalent for this task.\n\naudit-followup-closure:\n- source: docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0239-audit-r02.md\n- id: FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F1\n- state: tracked-existing\n- target: T-0981\n- rationale: Primary `T-0239` r02 accepted the current task and classified the metadata command serialization issue as a separate P3 release-management follow-up. `T-0981` closed the issue by aligning new generated preflight `metadata.json.command` with `command.txt`, covering `dotnet run`, `dotnet build`, `dotnet test` and `git diff` through RED/GREEN package output tests and saved primary audit `VERDICT: ACCEPT`.\n\n### Заметки агента\n\n2026-07-05T19:31:45+03:00 - Создано как `tracked-new` closure для `FOLLOW_UP_FINDING F1` из `docs/verdicts/release-management/t-0239-audit-r02.md`; control audit r02 для `T-0239` содержит только non-actionable `INFO_NOTE I1`.\n\n2026-07-07T13:05:00+03:00 - Ready-to-start gate пройден: `T-0981` была в `open`, зависимость `T-0239` принята и закрыта saved primary/control `ACCEPT`, внешний blocker отсутствовал.\n\n2026-07-07T13:12:00+03:00 - RED/GREEN завершён: `AuditPackageCommand` нормализует root preflight `metadata.json.command` в staging-копии, focused test покрывает `dotnet run`, `dotnet build`, `dotnet test` и `git diff`, доменный документ и generated docs index синхронизированы.\n\n### Архивное закрытие\n\n- 2026-07-07T13:40:00+03:00 - Primary r01 сохранён как `VERDICT: ACCEPT`, `RISKS_AND_NOTES` пусты; по явному решению пользователя first-try primary `ACCEPT` считается control-equivalent, поэтому отдельный control submit не выполнялся. Задача удалена из активного `TASKS.md` и перенесена в июльский архив.\n\n"
    }
  ],
